00:18:18.630 --> 00:18:20.000
Let's finish this off.

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:22.340
We have another translation
in here, and that's the

00:18:22.340 --> 00:18:30.240
translation T1 plus T2 over 2.

00:18:30.240 --> 00:18:36.840
So, what would we get if we took
the glide operation sigma

00:18:36.840 --> 00:18:43.740
one-half of T1 and followed
that by a translation T1

00:18:43.740 --> 00:18:45.920
plus T2 over 2.

00:18:45.920 --> 00:18:50.520
And that operation, again,
would be equal to a glide

00:18:50.520 --> 00:18:55.250
plane sigma prime with the tau
equal to the original glide

00:18:55.250 --> 00:18:59.500
component plus the part of the
translation that is parallel

00:18:59.500 --> 00:19:03.040
to the glide plane.

00:19:03.040 --> 00:19:06.980
And it'd be located at one-half
of the perpendicular

00:19:06.980 --> 00:19:10.330
part of the translation,
which is T2.

00:19:10.330 --> 00:19:14.820
So it'd be at one-half
of one-half of T2.

00:19:14.820 --> 00:19:18.050
So this says that the
combination of the glide

00:19:18.050 --> 00:19:22.060
operation with the centered
translation is a glide plane

00:19:22.060 --> 00:19:25.900
with a glide component T1.

00:19:25.900 --> 00:19:30.920
And it's located at
one-quarter of T2.

00:19:35.500 --> 00:19:42.390
And that, indeed, is what you
would do if you reflected and

00:19:42.390 --> 00:19:46.160
reproduced the object by a glide
down to here and then

00:19:46.160 --> 00:19:50.900
translated by T2 over to here.

00:19:54.570 --> 00:19:54.810
OK.

00:19:54.810 --> 00:19:55.270
No, I'm sorry.

00:19:55.270 --> 00:19:57.920
We glided and then we added on
